        "10:30": "This phase corresponds to the historical crossover point where skimmed and semi-skimmed milk consumption surpassed whole milk.",
        "10:55": "The growth is attributed to the solidification of social norms ('norms' set to True, 'social-conformity' at 0.28) and the weakening of initial incumbent habits over the 'memory-lifetime' of 5.0 steps.",
        "11:25": "The 'justification' mechanism (0.61) and cognitive processing allow agents to finally resolve dissonance in favor of the new, healthier norm."
      }
    },
